{"TopicId":112973,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Spring-loaded rocketry pt. 2","CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-14T22:14:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-14T22:14:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe altitude and general achievements of \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/125121-Spring-loaded-rocketry?p=2012252#post2012252\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Emy previous attempt\u003C/a\u003E were very meager. The capsule hardly rose above the point where the catapult would reach.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELet\u0027s try something else. I call it Project X-Bow!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETwo capsules for balance. Only one is kerbed.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/zWrfi4s.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022zWrfi4s.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe bow is drawn.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/DMONFZk.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022DMONFZk.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAaaand Lift-off!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/EG919yF.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022EG919yF.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELaunch confirmed!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/rPcyzr5.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022rPcyzr5.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReaching apoaxis!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/w6C0bCL.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022w6C0bCL.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AxlYxXu.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022AxlYxXu.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBeginning descent.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/dHZpHqj.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022dHZpHqj.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAnd successful landing!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/4mKY04v.jpg\u0022 alt=\u00224mKY04v.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ELet\u0027s have a look at mission stats:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/BhaHGKe.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022BhaHGKe.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/rIorYU8.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022rIorYU8.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA total of 219 meters upwards. Still a couple kilometers short of orbit but much better than the catapult!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Windspren","CreatedById":134441,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-14T23:53:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYou should try this with KAS winches. Compound bow, anyone?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LittleBlueGaming","CreatedById":144665,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-15T00:25:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ELol, you\u0027re crazy. I like it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"katateochi","CreatedById":35181,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-15T02:05:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EVery nice, I like where your heading with this!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E(a long time ago I made a rocket assisted catapult......and many Kerbals died -\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/9KlZlXwQppQ?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E)\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Laythe Dweller\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Laythe Dweller\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EYou should try this with KAS winches. Compound bow, anyone?\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile a compound bow would be awesome, I think building the pulleys would be hard. But I guess you could fake the pulleys with KAS winches....\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWith a recurve bow they are made out of layers of wood, so could you try having layers of girders (with many struts of course) and see if you can get a stronger bow like that? I suspect that it will probably just snap, but it might work.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kStrout","CreatedById":116630,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-06-15T02:10:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThrough extensive research and experimentation we may finally be able to use space age technologies to create ancient weapons! Now all we need is a huge Sword...\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}